# Day 8 – Lightning Web Components (LWC) Basics

## What is LWC?

Lightning Web Components (LWC) is Salesforce's modern framework for building fast, reusable, and lightweight user interfaces on the Salesforce Platform. It is based on modern web standards such as HTML, JavaScript, and CSS.

LWC allows developers to create interactive applications that run efficiently in Salesforce environments.

### Key Features of LWC

* Built on modern JavaScript standards.
* Fast performance and efficient rendering.
* Reusable components.
* Easy integration with Salesforce data.
* Secure and scalable architecture.
* Supports responsive user interfaces.

### LWC File Structure

```text
helloWorld/
│
├── helloWorld.html
├── helloWorld.js
├── helloWorld.js-meta.xml
└── helloWorld.css (optional)
```

---

## Why Salesforce Uses LWC

Salesforce introduced LWC to improve performance and align development with modern web technologies.

### Benefits of LWC

### 1. Better Performance

LWC uses native browser capabilities, making components load and render faster.

### 2. Reusability

Developers can create components once and reuse them across multiple pages.

### 3. Modern Standards

Uses standard HTML, CSS, and JavaScript instead of proprietary frameworks.

### 4. Improved Developer Experience

Developers with web development knowledge can quickly learn and build applications.

### 5. Enhanced Security

Works with Salesforce security models such as Lightning Locker and Lightning Web Security.

### 6. Seamless Salesforce Integration

Can easily connect with Apex classes, Salesforce objects, and platform services.

