## Component Breakdown

### HTML File (View Layer)

**helloWorld.html**

```html
<template>
    <lightning-card title="Hello World">
        <p>Hello Salesforce!</p>
    </lightning-card>
</template>
```

Responsibilities:

* Defines the user interface.
* Displays component content.
* Uses Salesforce Lightning Base Components.

---

### JavaScript File (Logic Layer)

**helloWorld.js**

```javascript
import { LightningElement } from 'lwc';

export default class HelloWorld extends LightningElement {
}
```

Responsibilities:

* Handles component logic.
* Manages data and events.
* Communicates with Apex if required.

---

### Metadata File

**helloWorld.js-meta.xml**

```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<LightningComponentBundle xmlns="http://soap.sforce.com/2006/04/metadata">
    <apiVersion>64.0</apiVersion>
    <isExposed>true</isExposed>
    <targets>
        <target>lightning__HomePage</target>
    </targets>
</LightningComponentBundle>
```

Responsibilities:

* Exposes the component to Salesforce.
* Defines where the component can be used.

