Through this exercise, I learned:

* How Salesforce components are structured.
* How HTML, JavaScript, and XML work together in LWC.
* How components are deployed and added to Lightning pages.
* The difference between frontend and backend responsibilities.
* The importance of reusable and modular design.

LWC is a powerful framework that helps developers build modern, responsive, and maintainable Salesforce applications. It improves performance, enhances user experience, and supports enterprise-level application development through reusable components and structured architecture.
